The meeting between ANC Secretary-General Ace Magashule and the Integrity Committee has concluded. Magashule appeared before the committee to answer questions about corruption charges he is facing. For more, Rofhiwa Madenza spoke to party spokesperson, Pule Mabe. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - ANC Secretary-General, Ace Magashule, has appeared before the party's Integrity Commission. The former Free State Premier says he was not forced to appear but he volunteered. READ: Magashule to appear before the integrity commission but what next? Magashule is currently facing 21 charges of corruption, fraud, and money laundering linked to his time serving as the Premier in the Free State. The commission is expected to outline the outcomes of the meeting. 